1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with a MIMO channel and proposes a coding scheme that achieves full diversity. This is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper proposes a communication scheme for a MIMO channel and evaluates its performance through simulations. This falls under the domain of communication and networking. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper employs signal processing techniques such as precoding and integer-forcing linear receiver. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses different QAM constellations, which is a common modulation scheme used in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses lattice coding, which is a type of data structure used in coding theory.
